"Lord Ram."

22
00:01:34,620 --> 00:01:35,447
Government hospital?

23
00:01:35,537 --> 00:01:36,953
Good morning, professor Govind.
- Yes.

24
00:01:37,953 --> 00:01:39,493
I said, good morning,
Professor Govind.

25
00:01:41,078 --> 00:01:42,328
You're mistaken.

26
00:01:42,620 --> 00:01:44,537
My name is Dharamprakash.

27
00:01:45,078 --> 00:01:46,578
Govind, Dharamprakash,

28
00:01:46,870 --> 00:01:48,828
Wilson, Srivastav, Deshpande...

29
00:01:49,203 --> 00:01:52,078
Choose any name,
it makes no difference to me.

30
00:01:58,870 --> 00:02:01,328
Adil Khan, Senior S.P. Bhopal.

31
00:02:02,493 --> 00:02:03,620
I know.

32
00:02:04,493 --> 00:02:07,245
I've been waiting for four years
to meet you.

33
00:02:07,620 --> 00:02:08,870
Shall we?

34
00:02:09,912 --> 00:02:13,287
There are many charges on him
from here to Nandighat.

35
00:02:13,537 --> 00:02:14,863
'Govind Ram Suryavanshi.'

36
00:02:14,953 --> 00:02:17,953
'He was born in a rich
business family in Mumbai.'

37
00:02:18,162 --> 00:02:20,870
'After passing out of the renowned
Doon School of our country,'

38
00:02:21,037 --> 00:02:24,245
'he studied at the
London School of Economics.'

39
00:02:24,703 --> 00:02:26,738
'After completing his doctorate
from Oxford University'

40
00:02:26,828 --> 00:02:27,828
'he returned to India.'

41
00:02:27,995 --> 00:02:29,863
'Touched by the exploitation
of the poor,'

42
00:02:29,953 --> 00:02:32,745
'he gave up everything
and joined the Maoist movement.'

43
00:02:32,995 --> 00:02:35,655
Mr Govind has been underground
for past 30 years.

44
00:02:35,745 --> 00:02:39,197
He's known as important ideologue
of the Naxal Movement.

45
00:02:39,287 --> 00:02:40,162
'Naxalism,'

46
00:02:40,287 --> 00:02:41,403
'which the Prime Minister
Manmohan Singh'

47
00:02:41,493 --> 00:02:45,245
'thinks the biggest threat
to internal security.'

48
00:02:45,537 --> 00:02:48,870
'More than 200 districts in the
country is affected by it.'

49
00:02:49,162 --> 00:02:51,328
'It all started 45 years ago'

50
00:02:51,493 --> 00:02:53,078
'in Naxalbari,
a village in Bengal,'

51
00:02:53,203 --> 00:02:56,197
'when poor farmers killed a
landlord'

52
00:02:56,287 --> 00:02:57,787
'to swan their right
over their land.'

53
00:02:58,413 --> 00:03:00,537
'Naxalism started from there.'

54
00:03:00,662 --> 00:03:02,822
'Naxalism has spread to
East Karnataka, Andhra Pradesh,'

55
00:03:02,912 --> 00:03:04,662
'Maharashtra, Bengal, Bihar,'

56
00:03:04,787 --> 00:03:08,537
'Odisha, Jharkhand,
and many other states.'

57
00:03:08,828 --> 00:03:11,493
'Thousands of tribals
have taken up arms.'

58
00:03:11,662 --> 00:03:13,995
'They are fighting against
the system of the country.'

59
00:03:14,203 --> 00:03:16,403
'It is believed that the tribals'

60
00:03:16,493 --> 00:03:17,953
'are given'

61
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:21,662
'arms and training from terrorist
organisations in India and abroad.'

62
00:03:21,953 --> 00:03:24,953
'The reason for the increase
of Naxalism in these areas is that'

63
00:03:25,078 --> 00:03:27,537
'there's been no development here
for the last 65 years.'

64
00:03:28,203 --> 00:03:30,403
'Today you speak of development'

65
00:03:30,493 --> 00:03:33,370
'only because under that pretext,
you want to seize their land'

66
00:03:34,078 --> 00:03:37,370
'which is rich in iron,
manganese, coal,'

67
00:03:37,578 --> 00:03:40,287
'bauxite and many other minerals.'

68
00:03:40,453 --> 00:03:41,537
Look,

69
00:03:41,745 --> 00:03:43,287
it is simple,

70
00:03:43,953 --> 00:03:47,953
unless we utilise these
natural resources in the land,

71
00:03:48,078 --> 00:03:49,703
how can there be development?

72
00:03:50,493 --> 00:03:52,537
That is why we are signing

73
00:03:52,703 --> 00:03:55,578
this 15 billion agreement with

74
00:03:55,787 --> 00:03:58,328
the huge Mahanta Group!

75
00:03:58,493 --> 00:04:01,828
And the rehabilitation plan
for the tribals is ready.

76
00:04:02,953 --> 00:04:07,203
As Chairman of the Mahanta Group,
I want to assure you all that

77
00:04:07,662 --> 00:04:11,413
the needs of Nandighat
people will be fulfilled.

78
00:04:11,578 --> 00:04:13,578
Concrete houses for the tribals,

79
00:04:13,745 --> 00:04:16,578
hospitals, an international school,

80
00:04:16,745 --> 00:04:19,162
and a world class university.

81
00:04:20,037 --> 00:04:21,363
Along with business,

82
00:04:21,453 --> 00:04:25,197
the Mahanta Group takes its social
responsibility very seriously.

83
00:04:25,287 --> 00:04:26,413
Mr Mahanta,

84
00:04:26,995 --> 00:04:28,870
will there be seats for

85
00:04:29,078 --> 00:04:30,662
tribal children in your
world class university?

86
00:04:30,787 --> 00:04:31,995
Look...
- Sir,

87
00:04:33,078 --> 00:04:35,537
it's obvious that the tribals
do not want to move.

88
00:04:35,662 --> 00:04:37,328
Will they be moved by force?

89
00:04:37,453 --> 00:04:38,370
Look,

90
00:04:38,493 --> 00:04:41,245
when the media succumbs
to Maoist propaganda,

91
00:04:41,620 --> 00:04:43,745
how will the public know the truth?

92
00:04:44,578 --> 00:04:46,703
The tribals are our brothers.

93
00:04:47,287 --> 00:04:49,328
No one can force them.

94
00:04:49,578 --> 00:04:51,662
Force will be used
only against the Naxals.

95
00:04:52,037 --> 00:04:54,870
Their menace will be wiped out
from Nandighat.

96
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:56,870
This is the government's promise.

97
00:04:58,037 --> 00:04:59,662
We are all ready.

98
00:04:59,995 --> 00:05:02,120
What I don't understand is

99
00:05:02,537 --> 00:05:05,120
while you advocate democracy,

100
00:05:05,745 --> 00:05:07,953
you're unwilling to speak with the

101
00:05:08,078 --> 00:05:09,738
government of the
world's biggest democracy.

102
00:05:09,828 --> 00:05:12,287
I don't believe in a democracy

103
00:05:13,078 --> 00:05:15,120
which doesn't respect the poor.

104
00:05:15,287 --> 00:05:16,572
We shall talk about your
extremist violence

105
00:05:16,662 --> 00:05:19,870
and police counter-violence
some other day, Professor.

106
00:05:20,828 --> 00:05:23,287
For now, I just want to ask
some basic questions.

107
00:05:23,537 --> 00:05:26,537
Before you waste your time
on meaningless questions,

108
00:05:27,328 --> 00:05:29,037
let me clarify,

109
00:05:30,037 --> 00:05:31,828
I only do three things now,

110
00:05:32,578 --> 00:05:34,245
reading, writing,

111
00:05:34,995 --> 00:05:36,078
and teaching.

112
00:05:37,537 --> 00:05:41,912
You can ask me any question
related to this, I will answer.

113
00:05:43,413 --> 00:05:45,037
Other than that,

114
00:05:45,828 --> 00:05:46,912
I won't say a word.

115
00:05:48,203 --> 00:05:50,120
And that's my right, too.

116
00:05:53,078 --> 00:05:55,828
Professor, if you choose to
stay quiet, fine.

117
00:05:56,370 --> 00:05:58,822
In my records,
you're responsible for the death

118
00:05:58,912 --> 00:06:01,287
of 91 policemen
and 150 innocent civilians.

119
00:06:11,413 --> 00:06:12,620
KK,

120
00:06:13,037 --> 00:06:14,745
how are things in Nandighat?

121
00:06:15,037 --> 00:06:16,245
Fantastic!

122
00:06:16,413 --> 00:06:19,703
You've shaken the entire Movement
by arresting Govind Suryavanshi.

123
00:06:20,287 --> 00:06:22,078
Did he give any information
about Nandighat?

124
00:06:22,245 --> 00:06:24,745
Not yet, but Rhea won't spare him.

125
00:06:25,828 --> 00:06:27,078
Give my regards to Rhea.

126
00:06:27,413 --> 00:06:29,822
By the way,
isn't your college reunion today?

127
00:06:29,912 --> 00:06:31,662
Yes, it will be a boring party.

128
00:06:32,037 --> 00:06:34,620
But we will have a blast tonight.

129
00:06:35,453 --> 00:06:37,370
Lots of fireworks.
- Why?

130
00:06:37,703 --> 00:06:38,953
Are you planning something?

131
00:06:40,245 --> 00:06:41,995
Is it an encounter? Tell me.

132
00:06:42,203 --> 00:06:45,493
I'll make an encounter to remember.

133
00:06:46,078 --> 00:06:49,162
I'll kill one such leader that
you'll be celebrating all year.

134
00:06:49,495 --> 00:06:50,905
Who? Rajan?

135
00:06:50,995 --> 00:06:52,203
Be patient, my friend.

136
00:06:52,995 --> 00:06:54,530
Read it in tomorrow's newspaper.

137
00:06:54,620 --> 00:06:55,953
I can't bloody wait.

138
00:06:56,453 --> 00:06:58,493
Get that rascal!
- 'I will.'

139
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:02,870
Who is it?
- Somebody named Kabir.

140
00:07:03,287 --> 00:07:04,287
Kabir?

141
00:07:04,495 --> 00:07:06,245
Hello, Kabir?
Is that really you?

142
00:07:06,370 --> 00:07:07,988
'The one and only!'

143
00:07:08,078 --> 00:07:10,947
Oh God, I don't believe this.
Where have you been, man!

144
00:07:11,037 --> 00:07:12,578
'I'm good. I'm here, Rhea.'

145
00:07:12,703 --> 00:07:14,078
Wow! Are you coming to the party?

146
00:07:14,413 --> 00:07:15,828
'Yes, but where is my friend?'

147
00:07:16,078 --> 00:07:17,537
Right here.

148
00:07:18,620 --> 00:07:19,662
It's Kabir!

149
00:07:20,537 --> 00:07:22,078
Even he is attending
the college party.

150
00:07:26,328 --> 00:07:29,120
You've been angry for 7 years.
It'll give you an ulcer.

151
00:07:29,287 --> 00:07:30,703
Can't you forgive him?

152
00:07:31,328 --> 00:07:32,495
You are acting like a kid.

153
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:35,787
'How can I say
what Kabir meant for me?'

154
00:07:36,493 --> 00:07:37,995
'He was more than a friend to me.'

155
00:07:40,203 --> 00:07:42,662
'He had no one else in this world,
but for me.'

156
00:07:44,620 --> 00:07:45,745
'What are you doing?'

157
00:07:45,953 --> 00:07:47,245
'I was day dreaming.'

158
00:07:47,413 --> 00:07:49,328
'I'm going back to the
government college now.'

159
00:07:50,413 --> 00:07:51,488
'As it is, the course was tough'

160
00:07:51,578 --> 00:07:53,162
'and now they have
raised the fees too.'

161
00:07:53,537 --> 00:07:54,995
'Your fees have been paid.'

162
00:07:55,703 --> 00:07:57,245
'I don't want your dad's money.'

163
00:07:57,662 --> 00:07:59,912
'I used dad's money
to pay my fees.'

164
00:08:00,245 --> 00:08:01,620
'With my scholarship,
I paid yours.'

165
00:08:11,245 --> 00:08:13,120
'What's this?
- Our future.'

166
00:08:17,493 --> 00:08:18,493
'Look boss,'

167
00:08:18,662 --> 00:08:20,572
'until now we did
everything together,'

168
00:08:20,662 --> 00:08:22,162
'but now our paths are different.'

169
00:08:22,328 --> 00:08:25,493
'Stop delivering dialogues
and just sign the form.'

170
00:08:26,370 --> 00:08:27,405
'But, I don't want to do this.'

171
00:08:27,495 --> 00:08:28,578
'No ifs and buts.'

172
00:08:29,413 --> 00:08:31,662
'I'll make you a cop,
come on, sign it.'

173
00:08:33,745 --> 00:08:35,745
'Freezing cold, torrential rains,
or scorching heat,'

174
00:08:35,870 --> 00:08:37,870
'in thunderstorms or floods,
night or day,'

175
00:08:38,245 --> 00:08:41,662
'once you're on duty,
nothing else matters.'

176
00:08:41,828 --> 00:08:43,370
'You have to stand,'

177
00:08:43,493 --> 00:08:45,037
'come what may.'

178
00:08:45,203 --> 00:08:47,413
'Sir, what do we do
if we want to pee?'

179
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:52,828
'Reform yourself, Kabir.
You joke all the time.'

180
00:08:53,745 --> 00:08:54,697
'Stop this nonsense.'

181
00:08:54,787 --> 00:08:55,863
'You are speaking nonsense.'

182
00:08:55,953 --> 00:08:57,828
'Your seats are reserved...
- No, Kabir!'

183
00:08:57,953 --> 00:09:00,537
'One moment.
- What are you doing, Mahesh?'

184
00:09:00,662 --> 00:09:01,870
'Let him go.'

185
00:09:01,995 --> 00:09:05,238
'This is not the way to talk to a
weak person. - Who are you?'

186
00:09:05,328 --> 00:09:07,280
'I had asked Kabir
not to get involved in any fights.'

187
00:09:07,370 --> 00:09:08,447
'Let it be, Kabir.'

188
00:09:08,537 --> 00:09:10,828
'And not ruin his life
over petty fights. - Stop it!'

189
00:09:11,287 --> 00:09:12,447
'I said stop it!
- But Kabir...'

190
00:09:12,537 --> 00:09:14,238
'Leave him.
- I say leave him!'

191
00:09:14,328 --> 00:09:15,828
'He could never control himself.'

192
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:22,537
'I cannot apologise.'

193
00:09:23,620 --> 00:09:25,328
'This is how I am,'

194
00:09:25,495 --> 00:09:26,578
'and this is how I will be!'

195
00:09:26,870 --> 00:09:29,037
'If you knew this already,
why did you bring me here?'

196
00:09:29,162 --> 00:09:31,238
'I made a mistake! A big mistake!'

197
00:09:31,328 --> 00:09:32,572
'Dad was right.'

198
00:09:32,662 --> 00:09:34,037
'You can never achieve something.'

199
00:09:34,328 --> 00:09:35,995
'Don't ever show me
your face again!'

200
00:09:43,828 --> 00:09:45,203
'After all these years...'

201
00:09:45,493 --> 00:09:47,413
'I don't know where was he,
what was he up to.'

202
00:09:48,787 --> 00:09:50,703
'Now, he shows up himself.'

203
00:09:52,413 --> 00:09:54,405
'Does he think
I'll give him a hug?'

204
00:09:54,495 --> 00:09:55,620
Kabir!

205
00:09:59,493 --> 00:10:01,078
This guy...

206
00:10:03,537 --> 00:10:06,203
Forgive me, my lord and master!

207
00:10:06,453 --> 00:10:08,287
I will never disobey you!

208
00:10:08,493 --> 00:10:09,620
You're my master.

209
00:10:09,787 --> 00:10:12,578
If you don't forgive me today,
I'll kill myself.

210
00:10:12,787 --> 00:10:14,745
I'll do everything you say.

211
00:10:15,203 --> 00:10:16,703
Stop being melodramatic.

212
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:23,413
Nothing much...

213
00:10:23,662 --> 00:10:25,413
I did some boring jobs for a while

214
00:10:25,912 --> 00:10:27,745
then joined an electronics company.

215
00:10:28,995 --> 00:10:31,620
And then, I started making
my own mobile phones.

216
00:10:32,703 --> 00:10:34,037
What, mobile phones?
- Yes.

217
00:10:34,662 --> 00:10:35,787
Your own brand?

218
00:10:36,703 --> 00:10:38,037
Have you ever tried this handset?

219
00:10:39,037 --> 00:10:40,037
RAK?

220
00:10:40,370 --> 00:10:41,703
What is RAK mobile?

221
00:10:44,245 --> 00:10:45,495
You'll never reform.

222
00:10:46,413 --> 00:10:48,037
R.A.K.

223
00:10:48,495 --> 00:10:50,203
Rhea, Adil, Kabir!
- Yes!

224
00:10:50,328 --> 00:10:52,197
No wonder it flopped.

225
00:10:52,287 --> 00:10:53,578
Flopped?

226
00:10:53,870 --> 00:10:57,493
The first consignment sold out
in MP and Chhattisgarh in a jiffy.

227
00:10:58,912 --> 00:11:02,703
But after two months...
there were complaints

228
00:11:03,245 --> 00:11:04,912
and the dealers stopped paying.

229
00:11:05,493 --> 00:11:07,287
The bank guys came home.

230
00:11:07,828 --> 00:11:08,870
I had a fight with them.

231
00:11:10,328 --> 00:11:12,953
I ended up hitting a cop.

232
00:11:13,162 --> 00:11:14,537
They arrested me.

233
00:11:15,037 --> 00:11:16,162
You hit a cop?

234
00:11:17,037 --> 00:11:18,037
Well done.

235
00:11:18,493 --> 00:11:20,037
So, for how long
were you locked up?

236
00:11:20,787 --> 00:11:22,280
Let it be.

237
00:11:22,370 --> 00:11:23,662
At least he's back.

238
00:11:24,413 --> 00:11:25,287
Good evening, sir.

239
00:11:25,453 --> 00:11:28,493
12 km from here, a village fair
is being held at Tulasi mountain.

240
00:11:28,703 --> 00:11:31,995
We got information that the Naxals
are holding a zonal meet there.

241
00:11:32,162 --> 00:11:34,613
Central Committee members, Shivram
and Chakravarthy are expected.

242
00:11:34,703 --> 00:11:37,120
The Zonal Commander,
Rajan, will also be present.

243
00:11:37,328 --> 00:11:38,328
Rajan?

244
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:40,162
How true is your information?

245
00:11:40,287 --> 00:11:42,947
We've cross checked it, sir.
Intelligence has confirmed it too.

246
00:11:43,037 --> 00:11:45,162
They're planning to retaliate
against Govind's arrest.

247
00:11:45,287 --> 00:11:46,287
Alright.

248
00:11:47,037 --> 00:11:48,370
Keep me informed.

249
00:11:48,828 --> 00:11:50,197
I will be in the Control Room
in an hour's time.

250
00:11:50,287 --> 00:11:51,287
Right, sir.

251
00:11:59,453 --> 00:12:01,493
Sir, please leave from there.

252
00:12:01,912 --> 00:12:03,912
Comrades have gathered
behind the temple.

253
00:12:04,287 --> 00:12:05,703
Their meeting is about to begin.

254
00:12:05,870 --> 00:12:07,203
'Sir, Kamal Kishor here.'

255
00:12:08,078 --> 00:12:09,662
Hello KK, Rathod here.

256
00:12:09,787 --> 00:12:10,787
'Good evening, sir.'

257
00:12:10,912 --> 00:12:12,037
We have the confirmation.

258
00:12:12,495 --> 00:12:13,537
Rajan is here.

259
00:12:13,787 --> 00:12:15,493
He's 400 yards away
from the target.

260
00:12:15,620 --> 00:12:16,620
Good, very good, KK.

261
00:12:16,912 --> 00:12:18,662
Don't let Rajan get away, SP!

262
00:12:18,912 --> 00:12:21,203
Kill him in an encounter.
Just finish him!

263
00:12:22,493 --> 00:12:25,495
That was the
Home Minister speaking, KK.

264
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:27,370
Sir.

265
00:12:27,828 --> 00:12:29,953
Be very careful, KK.
- Sir.

266
00:13:00,078 --> 00:13:01,912
KK, can you hear me?

267
00:13:02,078 --> 00:13:03,537
Try the second line.
Hurry up!

268
00:13:03,662 --> 00:13:04,662
KK!

269
00:13:21,745 --> 00:13:29,162
"Always be prepared
for the worst..."

270
00:13:34,578 --> 00:13:36,078
KK, can you hear me?

271
00:13:36,495 --> 00:13:37,495
KK...
- Oh God!

272
00:13:37,703 --> 00:13:39,453
Sir...
- KK, can you hear us?

273
00:13:40,328 --> 00:13:41,995
Sir, it's a trap.
We are surrounded.

274
00:13:42,995 --> 00:13:44,953
Hello, KK?

275
00:13:50,662 --> 00:13:52,787
'No entry'

276
00:13:54,912 --> 00:13:56,828
Lal Salam! (Red Salute)
- Lal Salam!

277
00:13:59,037 --> 00:14:01,037
Lal Salam!

278
00:14:01,828 --> 00:14:03,745
Lal Salam!

279
00:14:10,078 --> 00:14:11,030
Excuse me, sir.

280
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:13,447
Sir, can you tell us
about the massacre...

281
00:14:13,537 --> 00:14:15,662
Sir, can you please tell us

282
00:14:15,787 --> 00:14:16,745
which group has done this?

283
00:14:16,870 --> 00:14:19,162
Sir...
- We're investigating the matter.

284
00:14:19,413 --> 00:14:21,403
We'll talk with you later.
- Sir...

285
00:14:21,493 --> 00:14:23,863
Sir, can you please tell us how long
it will take for the investigation?

286
00:14:23,953 --> 00:14:25,947
'The massacre of 84 policemen,'

287
00:14:26,037 --> 00:14:28,403
'paramilitary personnel
at Nandighat is confirmed.'

288
00:14:28,493 --> 00:14:31,245
'Their funeral with state honours'

289
00:14:31,453 --> 00:14:33,323
'will take place
at 4 o'clock today.'

290
00:14:33,413 --> 00:14:35,328
'Meanwhile, Naxalite leader Rajan'

291
00:14:35,453 --> 00:14:38,280
'spoke to the media
at an unidentified location.'

292
00:14:38,370 --> 00:14:40,495
'We wish to declare
before the world,'

293
00:14:41,162 --> 00:14:43,870
'though the stooges
of the government'

294
00:14:44,037 --> 00:14:46,703
'falsely label us
murderers and terrorists,'

295
00:14:46,912 --> 00:14:50,662
'every attack of ours
is in defence of poor tribals'

296
00:14:50,995 --> 00:14:54,120
'who have been crushed
by the police and the state.'

297
00:14:54,995 --> 00:14:59,537
'We will not allow the government to
take even one inch of tribal land.'

298
00:15:00,578 --> 00:15:01,578
'Lal Salam.'

299
00:15:01,703 --> 00:15:04,613
'After the massacre of the
Nandighat, the Naxal zonal...'

300
00:15:04,703 --> 00:15:07,662
You have to take the responsibility
of this massacre.

301
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:09,287
But sir,

302
00:15:09,578 --> 00:15:11,787
the Home Minister himself
allowed the attack.

303
00:15:13,037 --> 00:15:14,745
He was in the Control room...

304
00:15:14,953 --> 00:15:16,537
When did I give you permission?

305
00:15:16,662 --> 00:15:17,912
Did I say

306
00:15:18,078 --> 00:15:20,078
the information is accurate
and send them charging?

307
00:15:21,203 --> 00:15:23,745
In fact,
you conned me into it, DGP.

308
00:15:24,953 --> 00:15:28,493
Please, don't blame me
for your failure.

309
00:15:28,662 --> 00:15:31,245
'This incident raises questions
about the Mahanta deal.'

310
00:15:31,493 --> 00:15:33,072
'Prashant Mahanta, the Chairman
of the Mahanta Group'

311
00:15:33,162 --> 00:15:35,703
'has called a press conference.'

312
00:15:35,953 --> 00:15:38,328
'We take you to his headquarters.'

313
00:15:38,453 --> 00:15:40,953
'Where even the police
and CRPF aren't safe,'

314
00:15:41,493 --> 00:15:44,203
'how can we risk setting up
a plant there?'

315
00:15:44,745 --> 00:15:48,493
'Until the government guarantees
the life of every worker,'

316
00:15:48,953 --> 00:15:51,572
'we will not begin any work.'

317
00:15:51,662 --> 00:15:53,403
'After Mahanta's statement...'

318
00:15:53,493 --> 00:15:55,328
Tell us, DGP,

319
00:15:55,493 --> 00:15:57,953
are you capable of dealing
with this problem

320
00:15:58,162 --> 00:15:59,620
or do I ask Mr Mahanta

321
00:15:59,787 --> 00:16:01,787
to sign the agreement
with Rajan instead?

322
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:05,203
Show some action, DGP.

323
00:16:05,537 --> 00:16:06,537
Action.

324
00:16:08,995 --> 00:16:09,995
Sir.

325
00:16:10,493 --> 00:16:12,995
Instant retaliation will have
its own complications.

326
00:16:13,493 --> 00:16:16,995
The enemy is not waiting at the
border whom we can attack.

327
00:16:17,453 --> 00:16:20,787
This massacre has emotionally
disturbed our men.

328
00:16:22,328 --> 00:16:24,120
Driven by vengeance,
they may commit excesses,

329
00:16:24,493 --> 00:16:25,870
and innocents will die.

330
00:16:26,078 --> 00:16:27,238
That will provoke
the tribals further,

331
00:16:27,328 --> 00:16:28,447
which is what the Naxals want.

332
00:16:28,537 --> 00:16:29,787
I know, Adil,

333
00:16:30,370 --> 00:16:32,912
but these politicians
have their own compulsions.

334
00:16:33,703 --> 00:16:35,403
To fulfil their selfish motives,

335
00:16:35,493 --> 00:16:36,828
they keep pressurising us.

336
00:16:36,953 --> 00:16:39,328
Do they even care
how many men we have lost?

337
00:16:41,413 --> 00:16:43,370
We lost such a brave officer
like KK.

338
00:16:44,453 --> 00:16:46,203
They will hand out
a little compensation

339
00:16:46,328 --> 00:16:47,953
for publicity, that's all.

340
00:16:49,037 --> 00:16:50,493
In such a terrible situation,

341
00:16:51,287 --> 00:16:53,078
who'd want to go to Nandighat?

342
00:16:53,745 --> 00:16:55,703
What? How can you do this?

343
00:16:56,037 --> 00:16:58,403
You took such a big decision
without even discussing it with me?

344
00:16:58,493 --> 00:16:59,578
I can't understand.

345
00:16:59,745 --> 00:17:01,120
Even I can't understand, Rhea.

346
00:17:02,037 --> 00:17:04,620
How can 84 policemen be
killed in one night?

347
00:17:04,912 --> 00:17:06,280
And how Nandighat

348
00:17:06,370 --> 00:17:08,495
is ruled by terrorists
instead of the state?

349
00:17:10,328 --> 00:17:12,662
Why nobody wants to be
posted there as the SP?

350
00:17:13,870 --> 00:17:14,953
Look Rhea,

351
00:17:16,037 --> 00:17:17,120
someone's got to do this.

352
00:17:17,287 --> 00:17:18,405
Right.

353
00:17:18,495 --> 00:17:20,787
And you're the only one who
can move this mountain, right?

354
00:17:20,912 --> 00:17:23,328
There is no other man in the
entire police department, right?

355
00:17:24,953 --> 00:17:26,162
Talk to her.

356
00:17:26,620 --> 00:17:27,953
She is overreacting.

357
00:17:28,203 --> 00:17:29,828
Obviously, she will.

358
00:17:30,078 --> 00:17:31,493
What you're doing is foolishness.

359
00:17:33,203 --> 00:17:35,245
It was so tough to get
a posting in the same city.

360
00:17:35,413 --> 00:17:38,037
We had just spoken
about starting a family

361
00:17:38,370 --> 00:17:40,287
and he took a
transfer to Nandighat!

362
00:17:44,328 --> 00:17:45,745
Don't do this, Adil.

363
00:17:46,370 --> 00:17:48,245
I don't see anything good in this.

364
00:18:04,620 --> 00:18:06,120
'Nandighat'

365
00:18:09,162 --> 00:18:11,245
Which route are you taking?
- Main highway, sir.

366
00:18:11,413 --> 00:18:12,662
It is safer.

367
00:18:13,287 --> 00:18:14,620
No, we will go via Lakhimpur.

368
00:18:14,912 --> 00:18:17,037
But the forest there...
- So?

369
00:18:28,912 --> 00:18:30,537
'This is our territory.'

370
00:18:31,162 --> 00:18:34,662
'Policemen,
enter at your own risk'.

371
00:18:35,162 --> 00:18:37,703
'They are responsible
for their death'.

372
00:18:47,078 --> 00:18:50,078
How far is Lakhimpur from here?
- About 4-5 km, sir.

373
00:18:53,787 --> 00:18:55,403
Drive down the slope,
it'll pass through.

374
00:18:55,493 --> 00:18:56,745
But, sir...

375
00:18:57,413 --> 00:18:58,620
Take it down, Rajaram.

376
00:18:59,287 --> 00:19:00,287
Give me the keys.

377
00:19:00,537 --> 00:19:01,703
Get back in.

378
00:19:01,995 --> 00:19:03,078
Come, sir.

379
00:19:40,953 --> 00:19:44,912
'Police station'

380
00:19:51,453 --> 00:19:53,078
Why is the gate locked?
- I'll check, sir.

381
00:19:56,078 --> 00:19:57,078
Open!
- Sir.

382
00:19:57,328 --> 00:19:58,447
The keys are with the Inspector.

383
00:19:58,537 --> 00:20:00,787
Hurry up.
Tell Tewari the SP is here.

384
00:20:00,912 --> 00:20:02,078
Sir.

385
00:20:02,703 --> 00:20:04,120
Sorry, sir.

386
00:20:06,493 --> 00:20:08,328
Is this a police station
or a den of thieves?

387
00:20:14,703 --> 00:20:17,493
Sir. - How much area does
Lakhimpur police station cover?

388
00:20:17,620 --> 00:20:19,453
2 km, sir.
- What?

389
00:20:19,662 --> 00:20:21,203
2 km?
- Yes, sir.

390
00:20:22,245 --> 00:20:24,870
But the next police station
is 23 km from here.

391
00:20:25,245 --> 00:20:28,995
There are roadblocks in each
direction 2 km from here.

392
00:20:29,245 --> 00:20:30,453
The staff fears to go there.

393
00:20:31,245 --> 00:20:33,537
Every new post we build,

394
00:20:33,745 --> 00:20:35,493
the Naxals blow it up
with dynamite.

395
00:20:37,037 --> 00:20:39,328
Then how do you get information
about the Naxals?

396
00:20:40,662 --> 00:20:42,162
Do you have informers in villages?

397
00:20:42,953 --> 00:20:44,493
How do you control crime here?

398
00:20:45,162 --> 00:20:46,745
Even if a murder is committed

399
00:20:47,078 --> 00:20:48,413
nobody reports it.

400
00:20:48,537 --> 00:20:51,537
All matters are settled in the
people's courts of the Naxals.

401
00:20:52,662 --> 00:20:54,703
It's very peaceful here, sir.

402
00:21:02,078 --> 00:21:03,493
Don't fire!

403
00:21:07,662 --> 00:21:09,078
Manager,

404
00:21:09,912 --> 00:21:11,703
came on your own?

405
00:21:12,495 --> 00:21:15,745
I thought you'd bring
the cops with you.

406
00:21:18,245 --> 00:21:20,197
Why do I need the cops,
when you're here, Mr Naga?

407
00:21:20,287 --> 00:21:22,493
When you're here...
- Manager,

408
00:21:23,493 --> 00:21:25,662
stop delivering dialogues.

409
00:21:26,828 --> 00:21:29,287
I'll put an end to your drama.

410
00:21:29,578 --> 00:21:32,828
Go ahead and plant the dynamite.

411
00:21:33,703 --> 00:21:35,822
Why are you getting angry, Mr Naga?

412
00:21:35,912 --> 00:21:39,037
We aren't outsiders. We'll listen
to... - Shut up, idiot!

413
00:21:40,245 --> 00:21:43,912
Your company buys this land for
pennies and mints billions, and we?

414
00:21:44,537 --> 00:21:47,655
We just ask for a donation of
2 million and you grumble.

415
00:21:47,745 --> 00:21:50,120
Give me a minute,
I'll arrange for it.

416
00:21:51,037 --> 00:21:53,995
That's all the time you have.
- Okay.

417
00:21:54,495 --> 00:21:57,328
Or in 60 seconds you'll be history.

418
00:21:59,453 --> 00:22:01,203
Hello...

419
00:22:10,620 --> 00:22:12,655
"Ravishing youth..."

420
00:22:12,745 --> 00:22:16,995
"I'm impressed with your beauty."

421
00:22:17,120 --> 00:22:19,493
"I can't do without you..."

422
00:22:24,912 --> 00:22:26,120
5...

423
00:22:30,662 --> 00:22:31,745
10...

424
00:22:32,828 --> 00:22:33,953
And...

425
00:22:34,413 --> 00:22:35,870
15. Total.

426
00:22:36,203 --> 00:22:37,953
Lal Salam!
- Lal Salam!

427
00:22:46,620 --> 00:22:47,953
Hey!

428
00:22:48,370 --> 00:22:49,370
What are you doing?

429
00:22:49,537 --> 00:22:51,828
I was taking my wages, Comrade.

430
00:22:52,413 --> 00:22:53,745
Is that so?
- Yes.

431
00:22:57,703 --> 00:23:00,578
That is what I like about you.

432
00:23:01,953 --> 00:23:05,203
You're very sharp with accounts.

433
00:23:06,328 --> 00:23:07,495
That I am.

434
00:23:09,120 --> 00:23:12,037
It is with your money that they
buy arms and ammunition.

435
00:23:12,745 --> 00:23:15,037
This amounts to a criminal
conspiracy against the state

436
00:23:15,328 --> 00:23:17,537
for which I can arrest you

437
00:23:17,745 --> 00:23:20,245
under section 120-B and 121.

438
00:23:20,453 --> 00:23:23,203
Sir, I'm Ravinder Nath. Project
Manager of Cosmos Global Steel.

439
00:23:23,537 --> 00:23:25,620
Our pipeline work was stalled
since the past 4 years.

440
00:23:26,037 --> 00:23:29,245
Sorry, but the police does not even
reply to our request for protection.

441
00:23:29,620 --> 00:23:31,037
We were losing millions every year.

442
00:23:31,203 --> 00:23:32,912
You tell us,
what option do we have?

443
00:23:33,328 --> 00:23:35,703
If we settle with the Naxals
and work, you kill us.

444
00:23:35,828 --> 00:23:37,245
If we don't,
the losses prove fatal.

445
00:23:37,370 --> 00:23:38,403
You tell us...
- We're helpless.

446
00:23:38,493 --> 00:23:39,447
Not only do we bear losses,

447
00:23:39,537 --> 00:23:41,162
but there is a threat
to our life as well.

448
00:23:41,287 --> 00:23:44,280
When there's a call from the
jungle, there's no cop in sight.

449
00:23:44,370 --> 00:23:45,162
You'll get it.

450
00:23:45,662 --> 00:23:47,745
You will get both,
police help and protection.

451
00:23:48,203 --> 00:23:50,162
But you too will have to help us.

452
00:23:50,953 --> 00:23:53,370
I want to cut the Naxals' supplies.

453
00:23:53,870 --> 00:23:56,537
They can't buy arms merely
with tribal donations.

454
00:23:57,493 --> 00:24:00,370
Remember,
we have to fight this war together.

455
00:24:00,703 --> 00:24:03,037
Our men don't understand politics.

456
00:24:03,493 --> 00:24:04,947
They can't understand

457
00:24:05,037 --> 00:24:08,370
why we're fighting against our
own countrymen and dying.

458
00:24:08,912 --> 00:24:11,703
They feel our politicians

459
00:24:12,120 --> 00:24:13,537
don't want a solution.

460
00:24:13,745 --> 00:24:15,245
We're being used as scapegoats!

461
00:24:15,413 --> 00:24:16,953
The condition of
the camps is so bad

462
00:24:17,162 --> 00:24:19,787
Sir! - that even if they
escape Naxal bullets,

463
00:24:19,912 --> 00:24:21,488
malaria will kill them.
- Sir!

464
00:24:21,578 --> 00:24:24,662
A posting in the interiors
means no electricity... - Sir!

465
00:24:24,787 --> 00:24:26,447
No network,
- Sir!

466
00:24:26,537 --> 00:24:28,655
They can't talk to their
families for months. - Sir!

467
00:24:28,745 --> 00:24:31,370
What about our intelligence?
- That's our biggest problem.

468
00:24:32,037 --> 00:24:34,113
If that was foolproof
KK and Sarabjeet

469
00:24:34,203 --> 00:24:35,120
wouldn't have been trapped.

470
00:24:35,453 --> 00:24:37,120
The scariest part is,

471
00:24:37,537 --> 00:24:40,120
the villagers support
the Naxals totally.

472
00:24:41,037 --> 00:24:43,245
We declared a reward
of 1.2 million,

473
00:24:43,370 --> 00:24:45,245
but nobody dares step forward.

474
00:24:45,578 --> 00:24:47,828
Since the Maoists
belong to the villages,

475
00:24:48,078 --> 00:24:50,287
they mix easily with them.

476
00:24:50,620 --> 00:24:52,403
Their network is so strong,

477
00:24:52,493 --> 00:24:54,413
they're aware of all our movements.

478
00:24:54,912 --> 00:24:56,745
It's only because of this
that Rajan

479
00:24:56,912 --> 00:24:59,370
and his two area commanders
Naga and Juhi

480
00:24:59,493 --> 00:25:01,912
have spread terror in Nandighat.

481
00:25:02,162 --> 00:25:04,995
We have to destroy
their control, at any cost.

482
00:25:18,328 --> 00:25:19,537
The police are here.

483
00:25:19,662 --> 00:25:21,162
Run!

484
00:25:25,745 --> 00:25:27,572
The police are here.

485
00:25:27,662 --> 00:25:30,493
The villagers have never seen
a government official.

486
00:25:30,912 --> 00:25:32,870
They think the police
is the government.

487
00:25:33,787 --> 00:25:35,995
They don't fear death as much as

488
00:25:36,245 --> 00:25:37,745
they fear the police uniform.

489
00:25:52,328 --> 00:25:54,162
Come, let's go.

490
00:25:54,413 --> 00:25:55,620
Let's go.
- Wait a minute.

491
00:25:56,037 --> 00:25:57,953
Listen.

492
00:25:58,245 --> 00:25:59,703
Run!

493
00:26:01,078 --> 00:26:02,403
Forgive me, sir.

494
00:26:02,493 --> 00:26:04,912
I don't know anything.
- Get the cot.

495
00:26:09,203 --> 00:26:10,787
I don't know anything.

496
00:26:10,953 --> 00:26:13,245
Come.
- Forgive me sir...

497
00:26:21,495 --> 00:26:22,620
Sit down.

498
00:26:24,870 --> 00:26:26,120
Sir...

499
00:26:29,370 --> 00:26:30,453
How did you get hurt?

500
00:27:21,493 --> 00:27:22,703
Please sit.

501
00:27:23,078 --> 00:27:24,780
Please sit.

502
00:27:24,870 --> 00:27:26,287
Sit.

503
00:27:27,162 --> 00:27:28,495
Sit.

504
00:27:31,328 --> 00:27:32,995
You need not fear.

505
00:27:34,828 --> 00:27:35,912
I am Adil,

506
00:27:37,787 --> 00:27:38,953
your friend.

507
00:27:40,245 --> 00:27:42,245
I admit we've made mistakes.

508
00:27:43,578 --> 00:27:44,995
The government did not pay
attention to your needs

509
00:27:45,120 --> 00:27:46,745
and there has been injustice.

510
00:27:47,537 --> 00:27:49,578
Even today,

511
00:27:50,745 --> 00:27:51,912
you fear the police.

512
00:27:52,203 --> 00:27:53,787
I'm here to rid you of that fear.

513
00:27:54,745 --> 00:27:57,620
With your cooperation,
we can correct our mistakes.

514
00:27:58,578 --> 00:28:00,030
The government and the country

515
00:28:00,120 --> 00:28:02,037
want you to be a part
of our progress.

516
00:28:02,828 --> 00:28:04,493
Your children should have
a bright future

517
00:28:04,870 --> 00:28:07,578
and not live under the shadow
of terror and guns.

518
00:28:08,953 --> 00:28:10,403
Think for yourself.

519
00:28:10,493 --> 00:28:14,120
What good have the
Maoists done by giving you guns?

520
00:28:14,287 --> 00:28:16,280
Roads, electricity,
school, hospitals,

